The paper discusses the intersection of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and community citizen science (cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.SI, cs.CSCW). The paper proposes a framework for community citizen science, which involves empowering communities to produce scientific knowledge, represent their needs, address their concerns, and advocate for impact. This framework involves the use of interactive systems, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction. The paper also discusses the importance of community engagement, which is relevant to the categories of community and society (cs.CY), collaborative and social computing (cs.CSCW), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
